cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on combining social media datasets (Twitter and YouTube) to gain insights into user behavior and video viewership. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper analyzes user behavior and social interactions on social media platforms. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the popularity and sharing of YouTube videos, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper focuses on video-centric data from YouTube and analyzes video content and viewership. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses user behavior and interactions on social media platforms, which can be seen as a form of human-computer interaction.
